  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Randomised control trial of 150 paediatric patients aged between 3-8years. One group will
      receive a preoperative carbohydrate oral drink and the other group will receive current
      standard care (no drink) prior to undergoing tonsillectomy and/or adenoidectomy.

      Outcomes to be reported will be: 1) patient and parent satisfaction; 2) post operative pain
      score at: recover, 1 hour post op, prior to discharge home and then day 1 postoperatively; 3)
      PONV rates in recovery, prior to discharge home and again on Day 1 postoperatively; 4) sleep
      quality night after surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Children undergoing tonsillectomy and/or adenoidectomy will be consented via parents prior to
      the day of surgery and then randomised to 1 of 2 groups who will either receive the
      intervention or current standard care. Patients will be recruited from the ENT outpatient
      clinics in conjunction with the ENT surgeons.

      Data collection will be undertaken with the aid of experience research assistants.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
